<div class="divider">
    <hr>
    <h2>Ready for CI</h2>
</div>

<p>Yeti can <a href="quick-start/index.html#Browser-launching">launch browsers with Selenium</a>
and provide <a href="quick-start/index.html#JUnit-XML-output">JUnit XML</a> results for easy
integration with CI systems like
<a href="http://jenkins-ci.org/">Jenkins</a> and
<a href="https://saucelabs.com/">Sauce Labs</a>.</p>

<p>Yeti is used at Yahoo! to run hundreds of thousands of tests in CI every day.</p>

<p>Yeti was made to test the YUI project on its
<a href="http://yuilibrary.com/yui/environments/">wide collection of target browsers</a>.
It currently works with IE 8+, Android 4+, iOS 4+, Chrome, Firefox, Safari,
and support for Android 2.3 and IE 6-7 is being worked on.</p>

